{
  "texts": [
    "A delicate approach is essential in the setting and derivation process of subgoals.",
    "Incorrectly set or conflicting subgoals can lead AI behavior in unforeseen directions; therefore, consistency and harmony among the goals must be guaranteed (Bengio et al. 2013).",
    "Especially in complex systems where multiple subgoals can be activated simultaneously, it's crucial to clearly understand and manage their interactions and priorities.",
    "For example, in the case of AI driving a car, conflicting situations can arise when subgoals like \"maintaining a safe distance from the car ahead\" and \"reaching the destination quickly\" are activated simultaneously.",
    "In such situations, AI must decide which subgoal to prioritize, and without clear criteria, it might engage in unexpected behavior."
  ]
}